Londen Wall & Will Kent
S on the 4 cur have writt to you & ordered some span clothes in
case they can come in time for the first convoj for ostend as also
for 12 worster frises to be forwarded as soon as possible by the
first departing convoij for holland, if that should depart before that
of ostend, yett if there was no appearence to have them departed befor
ses
the latter of this month, then not to send them, I orderinge oully
these frieses in hopes, that att recept of my letter at present op =
portunitie shall be, to forward them, where in I hope you will doe
mee punctuall service, if itt can not bee as I desire them lott them
allone, as for the flannels, lett them bedyed to the inclosed patt
& make them up to 30 a 35 a 36 p vez most about 16 & 3
Cntrsis
of 17: non exceeding 18 pence, I jay broad, white 20 a 24 p
12 dyed, yett if the dyed could not be readdy for the frrst convoy
for ostend, then lott the white come by them selfs, now I have
fours of 19 past & though you say, you have nothingh butt com
= plaints, yett fmust bell you, that I have opened this day
N48 & as longe as I have bived, have not seen worse cullour
then the 12 kersies they looke as if a dog had speidd them outt
of his stroad, & though they 12 6 en of such charges, they
do itt here 10 times better for 6 a p, therefore that tryall
is out for ever, & I am sure I shall not sell these under 4 o
losse, there fore minde better these flannels now ordered
further you say to be chore diligent about our bussines
then others, I am certaine of the contrarie, for I have also ope
ned this day the pack whites EE yeallow marks in N47: had
you looked them, I am sure you would have left out one p, which
is from one end to the other full of yeallow lines, not one yeard
without, so that that p can not serve our turne, & worse to mee
by £3:- & yett you will say I complaine, & nterim J ki am
changed which such goods & you know to well, that wee want no
pack whites, butt for religious habits, where in should not be
the least spots, I have had & seen manney houndreds EE yeallow
Marks, butt never one so as there is one a monghst these 5, so
that itt can not be that you minde my bussiness you self, or you
send mee such acloth to lof att mee, whoever if you can have
5 a 10 p EE yeallow marks that are pure white & good by the
iost convoy for ostend, provide them for mee, I have seen sever
all white Colchester bayes abive yeards broad, such as you
send to m gansacker & vermolen, best mee have 12 a 15 p of
them for atryall not exceedinge their prise, this white were
is soon readdy, & can easeley come by the first convoy for ostend
were in desire you to be diligent, letters are come from
England of 23 past butt non from you neither anney advise
of the convojes from hull god send them all o
